But he's nowhere to be found. As if swallowed by the earth.

177
00:21:48,709 --> 00:21:50,444
没希望了
It's hopeless.

178
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:55,849
还有什么线索吗 邮箱地址
What do you have? a PO box address.

179
00:21:57,484 --> 00:21:59,553
邮箱地址
A PO box address?

180
00:22:02,890 --> 00:22:05,292
试试彩票骗术
Try the lottery trick.

181
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,762
什么 彩票骗术
What? The lottery trick.

182
00:22:09,263 --> 00:22:12,599
写封信告诉他中了
Write to the PO box and tell him he's won...

183
00:22:13,300 --> 00:22:17,070
一部有GPS的手机 且他是选中的20人之一
... a monster cellphone with GPS and that he's one of 20 selected

184
00:22:17,805 --> 00:22:21,909
若他参加市场调查 就能赢10万奖金
to win 100000 if he'll participate in a market research study.

185
00:22:22,676 --> 00:22:24,344
这合法吗
Is it legal?

186
00:22:24,745 --> 00:22:27,581
难道送手机违法吗
It can't be illegal to give away a phone?

187
00:22:28,115 --> 00:22:31,385
就说你是因地戈市场调查部的
Say you're from Indigo market research.

188
00:22:41,495 --> 00:22:44,364
你好 亲爱的 对不起迟到了
Hi, honey. Sorry I'm late.

189
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:49,403
我们在赶下周的报纸 忙得要死
We're hitting the press next week, so we're fucking busy.

190
00:22:50,037 --> 00:22:53,140
报社只有你一个人吗
Are you the only one working in that paper?

191
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:55,901
每个人都忙得骡子样
Everybody's working like animals.

192
00:22:55,902 --> 00:22:57,277
我需要更多时间
I need more time than the others.

193
00:23:00,113 --> 00:23:03,383
米克开始跟一些买家对质
Micke has begun confronting some of the customers.

194
00:23:04,051 --> 00:23:07,621
他经验老道一定会把他们吓得尿裤子
He's so experienced they crap their pants if he just...

195
00:23:08,388 --> 00:23:11,425
完成了 出版了
It's finished. Printed. Yes.

196
00:23:11,992 --> 00:23:15,863
已经出版了吗 《平安出走俄罗斯》
It's already finished? "From Russia With Love".

197
00:23:16,630 --> 00:23:20,801
"集团犯罪和人口贩卖"
"Organized Crime and Human Trafficking".

198
00:23:21,635 --> 00:23:23,837
作者米娅·伯曼 是我
By Mia Bergman. That's me.

199
00:23:24,338 --> 00:23:25,839
我的女朋友
My girlfriend.

200
00:23:28,842 --> 00:23:30,911
我们得庆祝一下 好啊
We have to celebrate. Yes.

201
00:23:31,445 --> 00:23:33,080
亲我下
Give me a kiss.

202
00:23:33,547 --> 00:23:36,617
亲我一下 好了
Give me a kiss. It's finished.

203
00:23:49,963 --> 00:23:53,500
美味佳肴 真的很棒 安妮卡
Lovely food. Truly lovely, Annika.

204
00:23:54,234 --> 00:23:58,071
为什么跟她说 是我煮的
Why do you tell her? I did the cooking.

205
00:23:58,806 --> 00:24:01,008
味道好极了 安妮卡
It's quite tasty, Annika.

206
00:24:01,542 --> 00:24:03,935
你为什么不结婚
Why don't you get married?

207
00:24:03,936 --> 00:24:06,547
别管他 安吉丽娜姨妈
Leave him be, aunt Angelina.

208
00:24:07,447 --> 00:24:09,783
他不想结 为什么
He doesn't want to. Why not?

209
00:24:10,317 --> 00:24:12,586
他这么帅
He's so handsome.

210
00:24:13,153 --> 00:24:16,456
米克勒你有女人吗 你得找个女人
Mikael, do you have a woman? You must have a woman.

211
00:24:17,124 --> 00:24:18,992
是的 我有女人
Yes, I have a woman.

212
00:24:19,493 --> 00:24:23,764
那娶她 我倒想 但她已经结婚了
So marry her. I'd love to, but she's already married.

213
00:24:28,035 --> 00:24:29,903
打扰你了吗
Hi, am I interrupting?

214
00:24:30,404 --> 00:24:33,841
没 我在妹妹家和她丈夫家人在一起
No, I'm at my sister's and half a platoon of her husbands family.

215
00:24:34,541 --> 00:24:37,544
听起来不错 关于照片
Sounds nice. About the pictures...

216
00:24:38,178 --> 00:24:42,282
报纸上要用 明天我和米娅要去达拉纳
They are on paper, and Mia and I leave for Dalarna tomorrow.

217
00:24:43,116 --> 00:24:45,586
我不知道是否应该让邮递员送去
I don't know if I should send them with a messenger,

218
00:24:46,220 --> 00:24:50,457
不 别叫邮递员 我马上就走
No, don't use a messenger. I'm leaving soon.

219
00:24:51,291 --> 00:24:53,327
我可以送你一程
I can give you a lift.

220
00:24:53,794 --> 00:24:55,796
我在你那儿停一下 太好了
I'll stop by. Great,

221
00:24:56,296 --> 00:24:57,698
还有件事
And one more thing.

222
00:24:58,131 --> 00:25:02,503
我想起个名字 一个叫萨拉的犯人
I want to run a name. A criminal named Zala.

223
00:25:03,370 --> 00:25:06,573
告诉他在我的论文里化名叫安东
Tell him he's Anton in my dissertation.

224
00:25:07,307 --> 00:25:10,511
听到了吗 别这么晚才给我新消息
Did you hear that? Don't give me new material this late.

225
00:25:11,178 --> 00:25:14,882
我知道 但我认为这能奏效
No, I know, but I think it can pay off.

226
00:25:17,985 --> 00:25:20,420
晚点再谈 好的
We'll talk about it later. Yes.

227
00:25:37,004 --> 00:25:38,806
等我两分钟
Two minutes.

228
00:25:53,120 --> 00:25:56,256
怎么了 像是枪击
Did something happen? It sounded like a gunshot.

229
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:58,492
刚才
Just now.

230
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:02,095
道格
Dag?

231
00:26:03,463 --> 00:26:06,633
有人吗
Hello? hello?

232
00:26:37,831 --> 00:26:40,067
是你报的警吗
But you reported it?

233
00:26:41,635 --> 00:26:42,970
是的
Yes.

234
00:26:44,238 --> 00:26:48,609
你看到事发经过吗 没有 我发现了他们
Did you see what happened? No. I found them.

235
00:26:51,512 --> 00:26:55,282
遇害还不超过10分钟
It can't have been more than ten minutes after...

236
00:26:55,949 --> 00:26:59,119
你有什么要说明吗 看到有人逃离现场了吗
Do you have a description? Did you see anyone run away from the scene?

237
00:27:00,554 --> 00:27:02,256
没有
No.

238
00:27:03,957 --> 00:27:06,026
或许邻居会看到些什么
Maybe the neighbors saw something.

239
00:27:07,761 --> 00:27:09,329
你住这儿吗
Do you live here?

240
00:27:11,532 --> 00:27:15,669
不 来拜访住在这儿的那对情侣
No, I was going to visit the couple living here.

241
00:27:20,507 --> 00:27:22,276
一会儿回来
I'll be back.

242
00:27:22,743 --> 00:27:25,846
你好 布罗姆科斯特 请问你几个问题
Hello? Blomkvist? We have a couple of questions.

243
00:28:13,694 --> 00:28:15,596
你不能带电话进来
You can't have that here!

244
00:28:18,365 --> 00:28:22,069
这对受害者分别是记者和犯罪学家
The murdered couple was a journalist and a criminologist.

245
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:24,801
他们被千禧年的另一记者
They were found by another journalist.

246
00:28:24,802 --> 00:28:26,540
布罗姆科斯特发现的
Blomkvist from Millennium.

247
00:28:27,241 --> 00:28:29,843
作案动机是什么 目前还一无所获
What do we know about the motive? Not much at this point.

248
00:28:30,377 --> 00:28:32,946
那女的几周后就能拿到博士学位
The girl was about to get her Ph.D. in a couple of weeks.

249
00:28:33,547 --> 00:28:36,984
优先处理此案 召集特遣队
This case has the highest priority. Assemble a task force.

250
00:28:37,718 --> 00:28:39,783
汉斯·法斯特 杰克·侯伯格
Hans Faste, Jerker Holmberg.

251
00:28:39,784 --> 00:28:40,587
宋佳·茂迪
Sonja Modig.

252
00:28:45,058 --> 00:28:48,929
你可以自选组员 但行动要快
You can pick out the team yourself. But make it quick.

253
00:28:50,130 --> 00:28:52,499
伊克斯特 检查官
Eekstr? Prosecutors.

254
00:28:57,905 --> 00:29:01,675
你说杀手只是奉命行事
You described the murders as pure executions.

255
00:29:02,409 --> 00:29:04,631
这份名单上谁有这个能力
Which ones on the list are capable of that?

256
00:29:04,632 --> 00:29:06,046
且还能逃脱
And getting away with it?

257
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:10,250
我们正要曝光一些人
We're about to publish the names of several persons

258
00:29:10,951 --> 00:29:13,320
而他们不愿意被发现
Who'd prefer to stay out of the spotlight.

259
00:29:13,921 --> 00:29:16,557
道格已经联系了一些人
Some of them had already been contacted by Dag.

260
00:29:17,124 --> 00:29:19,020
这只是猜测
This is speculation.

261
00:29:19,021 --> 00:29:21,628
我们不该把名单交给警方吗
Shouldn't we hand the list over to the police?

262
00:29:22,463 --> 00:29:25,265
是的 我想应该这么做 不行
Yes I suppose we should. No.

263
00:29:28,969 --> 00:29:31,825
可以给他们一些买家的名字
They can have the names of some customers,

264
00:29:31,825 --> 00:29:34,541
但我们不能透露资料来源
but we must never reveal our sources.

265
00:29:35,500 --> 00:29:40,400
这是关乎被米娅访问过的女孩们的安全
It's about the safety of those girls Mia interviewed.

266
00:29:42,549 --> 00:29:44,718
这攸关生死
It can be life or death.

267
00:29:45,285 --> 00:29:48,622
要把这文章付印吗
Are we printing this?

268
00:29:51,758 --> 00:29:55,629
我认为那是道格的遗愿 同意
I think that's what Dag would've wanted. Agreed.

269
00:29:57,998 --> 00:29:59,700
克里斯特
Christer?

270
00:30:03,203 --> 00:30:04,972
当然
Sure.

271
00:30:54,421 --> 00:30:58,425
我们收到一份关于凶器的临时报告
We have received a temporary report about the murder weapon.

272
00:30:59,193 --> 00:31:03,263
非法的 不 绝对合法
It's illegal? No, it's perfectly legal.

273
00:31:03,997 --> 00:31:07,701
是属于尼尔斯·埃里克·彼尤曼律师的
It belongs to solicitor Nils Erik Bjurman.

274
00:31:08,469 --> 00:31:11,138
1983年买的 他在加尔代有房子
Aacquired in 1983. He's got an address on Gardet.

275
00:31:11,738 --> 00:31:13,240
立刻去那
There you go.

276
00:31:13,707 --> 00:31:16,844
且我们鉴定出两枚指纹
We could also identify two sets of fingerprints.

277
00:31:17,444 --> 00:31:19,947
一个1981出生的女人
A woman born in 1981.

278
00:31:21,748 --> 00:31:24,296
1998年在盖姆拉斯坦因袭击他人被捕
Arrested for assault in Gamla Stan in 1998,

279
00:31:24,296 --> 00:31:26,420
当时指纹被记录在案
when the fingerprints were taken.

280
00:31:27,254 --> 00:31:31,258
有名字吗 她叫丽莎白斯·萨兰德
Do you have a name? her name is Lisbeth...Salander.

281
00:31:35,162 --> 00:31:37,831
丽莎白斯·萨兰德好像挺棘手的
Lisbeth Salander seems quite disturbed,

282
00:31:38,432 --> 00:31:41,235
她有个法定监护人
She's under a legal guardian.

283
00:31:41,835 --> 00:31:44,238
猜是谁
Guess who the guardian is?

284
00:31:44,805 --> 00:31:47,027
尼尔斯·彼尤曼律师
Solicitor Nils Bjurman.

285
00:31:47,028 --> 00:31:48,509
安斯基得案凶器的持有者
The owner of the murder weapon in Enskede.

286
00:31:49,243 --> 00:31:51,678
她在学校就已经很粗暴
She was already violent in school.

287
00:31:52,212 --> 00:31:53,530
少年时曾接受精神治疗
Psychiatric treatment as a teen.

288
00:31:53,530 --> 00:31:55,782
我们认为她以卖淫为生
We think she supports herself through prostitution.

289
00:31:56,517 --> 00:31:59,386
且记录上写着有暴力倾向
And documented violent tendencies.

290
00:32:00,721 --> 00:32:02,907
我们有萨兰德的地址吗
We have Salander's address?

291
00:32:02,908 --> 00:32:04,925
斯德哥尔摩的伦德格坦
Lundagatan in Stockholm.

292
00:32:06,326 --> 00:32:09,163
站住 警察 过马路
Stop! Police. Cross the street.

293
00:32:09,797 --> 00:32:14,134
抓到萨兰德了吗 没 我们在等支援
Have you arrested Salander? No, we're waiting for backup.

294
00:32:14,902 --> 00:32:18,839
打给我 我们搞定后给你回话
Call me. I'll call when we're done.

295
00:32:21,375 --> 00:32:24,611
妓女们不再有社会地位
Hookers have no class anymore.

296
00:32:25,345 --> 00:32:28,549
她们每况愈下 你要逮捕她吗
They look more fucked up every day. Would you pick her up?

297
00:32:31,251 --> 00:32:33,887
有个更简单的方法
There has to be a simpler way.

298
00:32:34,454 --> 00:32:38,358
为什么要这么兴师动众
Why call in the storm troopers to catch one small fish?

299
00:32:39,126 --> 00:32:41,862
那女的身高1米5 体重40公斤
The girl is 150 cm tall and weighs 40 kg.

300
00:32:44,665 --> 00:32:47,468
我们进去了 但公寓是空的
We're in but the apartment is empty.

301
00:32:48,035 --> 00:32:49,670
已确认
Affirmative.

302
00:32:54,341 --> 00:32:56,510
法斯特 怎么
Faste? Yes?

303
00:32:57,044 --> 00:32:59,613
为什么门上写萨兰德·吴
Why did it say Salander Wu on the door?

304
00:33:02,182 --> 00:33:03,817
毫无头绪
Have no idea.

305
00:33:24,304 --> 00:33:26,995
你好 我是彼尤曼
Hello, this is Bjurman.

306
00:33:26,996 --> 00:33:29,443
请留言 稍后回复你
Please leave a message and I'll get back to you.

307
00:33:46,026 --> 00:33:47,361
有人吗
Hello?

308
00:34:05,712 --> 00:34:09,183
那个角度再照一张 那样更全面
Snap one from that angle as well, so we get it properly.

309
00:34:12,953 --> 00:34:14,621
她在那儿
She's in there..

310
00:34:23,130 --> 00:34:25,866
谢谢 我想死咖啡了
Thanks. My coffee craving was about to kill me.

311
00:34:26,533 --> 00:34:28,235
你有什么发现吗
What have you found?

312
00:34:28,702 --> 00:34:31,808
彼尤曼 还有一枚空的马格南枪弹壳
Bjurman, and an empty Magnum bullet box.

313
00:34:31,809 --> 00:34:32,973
我们在查指纹
We're checking it for prints.

314
00:34:33,807 --> 00:34:36,443
还有每月关于萨兰德报告的复印件
And copies of monthly reports on Salander,

315
00:34:37,044 --> 00:34:39,746
那是发送给监护中心
which he's been sending to the Guardianship.

316
00:34:41,915 --> 00:34:44,985
从报告看 萨兰德就是个天使
According to the reports Salander is basically an angel.

317
00:34:47,721 --> 00:34:51,492
我们把尸体翻过来了 你们得看看这个
We have turned him around. There is something you should see.

318
00:34:56,380 --> 00:35:00,300
我是个残暴的猪和强奸犯
"I am a sadistic pig and a rapist".

319
00:35:03,203 --> 00:35:06,540
你怎么看 不错的杀人动机
What do you think? Not a bad motive for murder.

320
00:35:17,584 --> 00:35:20,487
丽莎白斯 28岁 三起杀人案的通缉犯
LISBETH 28 SOUGHT FOR THREE MURDERS

321
00:35:31,031 --> 00:35:32,866
通缉安斯基得三起杀人案的凶手
Sought For Three Murders In Enskede

322
00:35:34,668 --> 00:35:36,136
通缉三起杀人案的凶手
Hunted For THREE MURDERS

323
00:35:40,674 --> 00:35:43,043
记者布罗姆科斯特发现凶杀案受害者
Journalist Blomkvist found the murder victims

324
00:36:04,198 --> 00:36:07,568
今天下午又一名受害者被发现
This afternoon another victim was found.

325
00:36:08,335 --> 00:36:10,274
56岁的资深律师
The 56 year old socially commited solicitor

326
00:36:10,275 --> 00:36:11,972
被发现在其公寓遇害
was found shot in his apartment.

327
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:17,878
警察正在调查这几起杀人案是否有关联
Police is investigating if the murders are connected.

328
00:36:18,779 --> 00:36:22,716
其中一位受害者在
One of the victims worked for the newspaper Millennium,

329
00:36:23,450 --> 00:36:26,620
布罗姆科斯特任总编的千禧年报社供职
where Blomkvist is editor in charge.

330
00:36:27,287 --> 00:36:31,458
据布罗姆科斯特称 史万森将要撰写
According to Blomkvist, Svensson was about to write about

331
00:36:32,259 --> 00:36:35,162
有关安全与黑客的报道
it security and hackers.

332
00:36:35,829 --> 00:36:39,867
这对他的家庭和同事
It's a great loss for his family and collegues

333
00:36:40,667 --> 00:36:43,337
还有整个新闻界都是个巨大的损失
and the whole journalist community.

334
00:36:43,971 --> 00:36:47,374
这是对自由社会的野蛮攻击
A brutal attack on free society.

335
00:36:49,009 --> 00:36:51,745
为什么告诉他们这些 那是真相
Why did you tell them that? Because it's true.

336
00:36:53,614 --> 00:36:56,083
道格的专题之一就是报导黑客攻击
One of dag's specialties was hacking.

337
00:36:56,617 --> 00:36:59,820
我们已经同意他的下个题目是这个了
We had agreed that it would be his next case.

338
00:37:00,487 --> 00:37:04,558
我想在警察之前找到某人
And I want to find a certain person before the police does.

339
00:37:05,325 --> 00:37:08,400
丽莎白斯会读我写的所有报道
Lisbeth reads everything I write.

340
00:37:08,401 --> 00:37:09,630
不论她在哪儿
No matter where she is.

341
00:37:10,464 --> 00:37:13,367
都会对这感兴趣的
And she's quite interested in the subject.

342
00:37:14,001 --> 00:37:17,704
这个发言也许能让她联系我
This statement might make her contact me.

343
00:37:18,505 --> 00:37:21,441
你不怀疑吗 怀疑什么
You have no doubts? About what?

344
00:37:23,177 --> 00:37:24,378
不
No.

345
00:37:27,514 --> 00:37:30,117
不 丽莎白斯没杀任何人
No? Lisbeth has not murdered anyone.

346
00:37:38,559 --> 00:37:42,696
道格的电话 我来接
That's Dag's phone. I'll get it.

347
00:37:50,471 --> 00:37:52,520
因地戈市场调查部
